        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "Every year you watched the ceremony of sacrifice, the priests hu8rried the still beating hearts up the temple steps. Every year they failed, because the men they chose were weak, and you knew it. You aspired to be the last one, the one who's heart would appease Tlazolteotl. Your chance came in time, after years or training and preparing your body and soul to be to their liking. You lived as Tlazolteotl should, in luxury, in gold, and in the arms of whomever you chose. But you had ideas, you wanted to change the rituals, the way the priests would run up the temple steps, how they'd hold the heart to assure the ritual would be successful. You bid it so. Their response was more wine, more songs, more trivial and earthly pleasures. You were outraged by such sacrilege, it should be sentenced to Death. But the songs, drugs, and wine were stronger than your mortal coi. The night of your sacrifice you knew your body was weak, and you understood the nature of the cycle. You were drugged to be weak so the heart failed the race, you began to fade when she approached you with a small cup, while the other priests left you behind to your fate. \"Drink, and rise to lead your people anew, my god.\" She told you. And you rose the next night anew, a god.Your oracle followed you North, warning you that these heretics would be destroyed by Quetzalcoatl incarnate for their foolishness. You watched together as Quetzalcoatl in his armor of shining armor and his men of screaming weapons as they destroyed the heretics and nonbelievers, the way God destroyed Sodom. Your oracle led you to the North where you were received by two more shamen, both of a different time and path of life, but they welcomed you in your new form, and you have been together since."
        ],
